DWM(1)                                      General Commands Manual                                      DWM(1)

NNAAMMEE
       dwm - dynamic window manager (Luke Smith <https://lukesmith.xyz>'s build)

SSYYNNOOPPSSIISS
       ddwwmm [--vv]

DDEESSCCRRIIPPTTIIOONN
       dwm is a dynamic window manager for X.

       dwm  "orders"  windows based on recency and primacy, while dwm layouts may change, the most recent "mas‐
       ter" window is shown in the most prominent position. There are bindings for cycling through and  promot‐
       ing windows to the master position.

       Windows are grouped by tags. Each window can be tagged with one or multiple tags. Selecting certain tags
       displays all windows with these tags.

       Each screen contains a small status bar which displays all available tags, the layout, the title of  the
       focused window, and the text read from the root window name property, if the screen is focused. A float‐
       ing window is indicated with an empty square and a maximised floating window is indicated with a  filled
       square  before  the  windows title.  The selected tags are indicated with a different color. The tags of
       the focused window are indicated with a filled square in the top left corner.  The tags  which  are  ap‐
       plied to one or more windows are indicated with an empty square in the top left corner.

       dwm draws a small border around windows to indicate the focus state.

       _l_i_b_x_f_t_-_b_g_r_a  should  be  installed  for  this build of dwm. Arch users may install it via the AUR. Color
       characters and emoji are enabled, but these will cause crashes without the fix _l_i_b_x_f_t_-_b_g_r_a offers.

OOPPTTIIOONNSS
       --vv     prints version information to standard output, then exits.

UUSSAAGGEE
   SSttaattuuss bbaarr
       XX rroooott wwiinnddooww nnaammee
              is read and displayed in the status text area. It can be set with the xxsseettrroooott(1) command.

       LLeefftt cclliicckk
              click on a tag label to display all windows with that tag, click on the layout label toggles  be‐
              tween tiled and floating layout.

       RRiigghhtt cclliicckk
              click on a tag label adds/removes all windows with that tag to/from the view.

       SSuuppeerr--LLeefftt cclliicckk
              click on a tag label applies that tag to the focused window.

       SSuuppeerr--RRiigghhtt cclliicckk
              click on a tag label adds/removes that tag to/from the focused window.

   KKeeyybbooaarrdd ccoommmmaannddss
       SSuuppeerr--RReettuurrnn
              Start terminal, sstt((11))..

       SSuuppeerr--dd
              Spawn ddmmeennuu((11)) for launching other programs.

       SSuuppeerr--bb
              Toggles bar on and off.

       SSuuppeerr--qq
              Close focused window.

       SSuuppeerr--tt//TT
              Sets tiled/bstack layouts.

       SSuuppeerr--ff
              Toggle fullscreen window.

       SSuuppeerr--FF
              Toggle floating layout.

       SSuuppeerr--yy//YY
              Sets Fibonacci spiral/dwinde layouts.

       SSuuppeerr--uu//UU
              Sets centered master layout.

       SSuuppeerr--ii//II
              Sets centered master or floating master layouts.

       SSuuppeerr--ssppaaccee
              Zooms/cycles focused window to/from master area.

       SSuuppeerr--jj//kk
              Focus next/previous window.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--jj//kk
              Move selected window down/up in stack.

       SSuuppeerr--oo//OO
              Increase/decrease number of windows in master area.

       SSuuppeerr--ll
              Increase master area size.

       SSuuppeerr--hh
              Decrease master area size.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--ssppaaccee
              Toggle focused window between tiled and floating state.

       SSuuppeerr--TTaabb
              Toggles to the previously selected tags.

       SSuuppeerr--gg
              Moves to the previous tag.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--gg
              Moves selected window to the previous tag.

       SSuuppeerr--;;
              Moves to the next tag.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--;;
              Moves selected window to the next tag.

       SSuuppeerr--PPaaggeeUUpp
              Moves to the previous tag.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--PPaaggeeUUpp
              Moves selected window to the previous tag.

       SSuuppeerr--PPaaggeeddoowwnn
              Moves to the next tag.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--PPaaggeeDDoowwnn
              Moves selected window to the next tag.

       SSuuppeerr--aa
              Toggle gaps.

       SSuuppeerr--zz
              Increase gaps between windows.

       SSuuppeerr--xx
              Decrease gaps between windows.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--[[11....nn]]
              Apply nth tag to focused window.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--00
              Apply all tags to focused window.

       SSuuppeerr--CCoonnttrrooll--SShhiifftt--[[11....nn]]
              Add/remove nth tag to/from focused window.

       SSuuppeerr--[[11....nn]]
              View all windows with nth tag.

       SSuuppeerr--00
              View all windows with any tag.

       SSuuppeerr--CCoonnttrrooll--[[11....nn]]
              Add/remove all windows with nth tag to/from the view.

       SSuuppeerr--SShhiifftt--qq
              Quit dwm.

       MMoodd11--CCoonnttrrooll--SShhiifftt--qq
              Menu to refresh/quit/reboot/shutdown.

   MMoouussee ccoommmmaannddss
       SSuuppeerr--LLeefftt cclliicckk
              Move focused window while dragging. Tiled windows will be toggled to the floating state.

       SSuuppeerr--MMiiddddllee cclliicckk
              Toggles focused window between floating and tiled state.

       SSuuppeerr--RRiigghhtt cclliicckk
              Resize focused window while dragging. Tiled windows will be toggled to the floating state.

CCUUSSTTOOMMIIZZAATTIIOONN
       dwm  is  customized by creating a custom config.h and (re)compiling the source code. This keeps it fast,
       secure and simple.

SSIIGGNNAALLSS
       SSIIGGHHUUPP -- 11
              Restart the dwm process.

       SSIIGGTTEERRMM -- 1155
              Cleanly terminate the dwm process.

SSEEEE AALLSSOO
       ddmmeennuu(1), sstt(1)

IISSSSUUEESS
       Java applications which use the XToolkit/XAWT backend may draw  grey  windows  only.  The  XToolkit/XAWT
       backend  breaks  ICCCM-compliance in recent JDK 1.5 and early JDK 1.6 versions, because it assumes a re‐
       parenting  window  manager.  Possible  workarounds  are  using  JDK  1.4  (which  doesn't  contain   the
       XToolkit/XAWT  backend) or setting the environment variable AAWWTT__TTOOOOLLKKIITT==MMTToooollkkiitt (to use the older Motif
       backend instead) or running xxpprroopp --rroooott --ff __NNEETT__WWMM__NNAAMMEE 3322aa --sseett __NNEETT__WWMM__NNAAMMEE LLGG33DD or  wwmmnnaammee  LLGG33DD  (to
       pretend  that  a non-reparenting window manager is running that the XToolkit/XAWT backend can recognize)
       or when using OpenJDK setting the environment variable __JJAAVVAA__AAWWTT__WWMM__NNOONNRREEPPAARREENNTTIINNGG==11.

